Yoruba movie star Saidi Balogun and his ex-wife, actress, Fathia Williams, on Saturday celebrated their birthdays. Faitha clocked 53 while Saheed is 55. They shared stunning pictures on their respective Instagram pages to mark their day. But checks by The Nation show the estranged lovers are yet to comment or felicitate with each other on their posts. Before their separation, Fathia and Saheed were married for six years. - Advertisement - Their marriage took place on September 7, 2000 at the Ikorodu Marriage Registry, Lagos.   Fathia Balogun visits destitutes for birthday     Moyo Lawal: Fans mistake my film character for my…     Actors, directors, producers speak on Nollywood’s…   The union produced two children. But in November 2017, Fathia reverted to her maiden name “Williams” after their divorce was finalised. In 2019, Fathia featured her ex-husband, Balogun, in a movie titled ‘Aje Oja’, which was the first time the couple would feature in the same movie in 14 years. Shortly after his divorce with Fathia, Saidi remarried Funke Elegushi, younger sister to Oba Saheed Elegushi of Ikate land, Lagos. The union also broke down. Saidi’s first wife Sherifat Balogun has two kids — Zinnat and Jamal.